Package: datawall
Version: 1.0.0
Architecture: all
Maintainer: Erysnell Gonzalez
Depends: python3, python3-psutil, python3-rich
Description: Track daily network usage per program
 datawall runs a lightweight background daemon that samples
 network traffic and attributes it to active processes.
 It provides a terminal UI showing per-program breakdown,
 total daily usage, and current transfer speeds with bars.
 .
 Features:
   * Per-program daily network usage (sent/received/total)
   * Real-time transfer speed display
   * Visual usage bars via Rich
   * Automatic active interface detection
   * Systemd user service integration
   * Real-time bandwidth monitor (datawall watch)
   * Historical reports for N days (datawall days N)
   * Daily traffic limit with visual alerts (datawall limit)
   * Live TCP connections viewer (datawall connections)
